**Welcome to the Reichsrat!**

This is the official organ that represents local state governments in the Reich-legislation. It can veto any law the government passes, so having them on ones side is always advisable.

{!<svg id="reichsrat_viz" style="width: 500px; height: 250px;"> </svg>!}

To appease the <span style="color: #00CCFF;">Bavarian</span> government and their allies the law was amended to make an interpretation of exclusive targeting of the <span style="color: [+ dnvp_colour +];">**right**</span> impossible.

- @go_with_the_new_text
- @make_a_lot_of_fuzz_about_the_wording

@go_with_the_new_text
title: We will pass the law with the new text.
subtitle: We really don't want another Kapp Putsch...
on-arrival: kpd_relation -= 2; uspd_relation -= 4; dvp_relation += 1; early_dvp_cooperation += 1*(1-dissent); reformist_strength += 3

The law passes! But the delegation from <span style="color: #00CCFF;">Bavaria</span> voted against it anyways...

Now we only have to adopt it in the Reichstag.

- @wow_easy_sweap

@make_a_lot_of_fuzz_about_the_wording
title: Demand the origianl wording
subtitle: This would not prevent attacks on worker's parties for certain. Furthermore the Bourgeois would be displeased.
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 2; uspd_relation += 10; z_relation -= 2; dvp_relation -= 5; early_dvp_cooperation -= 2; coaltion_dissent += 1; left_strength += 3

The law passes with a high abstention rate. Our coalition partners in the Reich and in Prussia accuse us of childish behavior and frightening closeness to the radical <span style="color: [+ kpd_colour +];">**KPD**</span>. Working with the <span style="color: [+ dvp_colour +];">**DVP**</span> will become way harder. Let's just hope we can get this law through the Reichstag.

- @damn_close_race_ok_wow

@wow_easy_sweap
title: The Reichstag will adopt the law.

The <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**SPD**</span>, <span style="color: [+ ddp_colour +];">**DDP**</span>, <span style="color: [+ z_colour +];">**Center**</span> and <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> vote entirely in favour of the law, the <span style="color: [+ dnvp_colour +];">**DNVP**</span> and <span style="color: [+ bvp_colour +];">**Bavarian**</span> parties unite against it. The <span style="color: [+ dvp_colour +];">**DVP**</span> is split but most vote in favour as a sign of good will towards the Republic as part of their <span class="tooltip-text" title="The official doctrine of the DVP under Stresemann - support the republic strategically but keep the Monarchy in heart" <span style="color: [+ dvp_colour +];">**Vernunftrepublikanismus**</span>.

The votes in favour outnumber those against by a factor of three. The <span style="color: #000000;">**Rep**</span><span style="color: #c10000;">**ub**</span><span style="color: #D3C24D;">**lic**</span> will be save for sure now.

@damn_close_race_ok_wow
title: Let's see if we can get it through the Reichstag as well...
on-arrival: super_mad_bavaria += 1

The <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**SPD**</span>, <span style="color: [+ ddp_colour +];">**DDP**</span> and <span style="color: [+ uspd_colour +];">**USPD**</span> vote entirely in favour of the law, the <span style="color: [+ dnvp_colour +];">**DNVP**</span> and <span style="color: [+ bvp_colour +];">**Bavarian**</span> parties unite against it. Despite most members voting in favour, some in the <span style="color: [+ z_colour +];">**Center**</span> have abstained alongside the <span style="color: #ADE06E;">**DHP**</span> and <span style="color: [+ kpd_colour +];">**KPD**</span>. The <span style="color: [+ dvp_colour +];">**DVP**</span> is split but most abstain. Yet they shy away from voting against because of their <span class="tooltip-text" title="The official doctrine of the DVP under Stresemann - support the republic strategically but keep the Monarchy in heart" <span style="color: [+ dvp_colour +];">**Vernunftrepublikanismus**</span>.

The 2/3 majority is secured but it took a lot of abstentions to pass a republican law in a republican parliament...



